Mike,
I wasen't implicating any dishonesty, just how in the heck coud anyone
possibly know that a throw out bearing, brake line, or anything fail?
It's an imposssibiity to note everything that could possibly go
wrong--and to some folks, even if you disclosed every item that you know
about, something else could go wrong and it would be your fault------  

This is life in the big city--and there's not much you could ever do to
satisfy some people--regardless of your honest disclosures--

Like I said--how old are these things?

How long are they supposed to go without failure of one sort or another
?

You just can't cover it all---

