Hence my caveat that "It's everything that I personally know is wrong
with the vehicle", and the big upper-case "AS IS" and "NO RETURN" on the
bill of sale. 
They sell a lot of used vehicles down here, so it's rather accepted that
there's probably going to be something wrong with it when it's sold.
It's just my own thing to be someone honest enough to fill you in before
you buy it. 
